@YaelDillies at this point in time I'm primarily interested in vector spaces over ℝ or ℂ, so I'd be happy to use `[RCLike 𝕜]`.

The `Analysis/LocallyConvex/AbsConvex.lean` currently in the main branch defines:
```
/-- The type of absolutely convex open sets. -/
def AbsConvexOpenSets :=
  { s : Set E // (0 : E) ∈ s ∧ IsOpen s ∧ Balanced 𝕜 s ∧ Convex ℝ s }
```
so I thought that my definition of `AbsConvex` needed to be sufficiently general that I could replace ` Balanced 𝕜 s ∧ Convex ℝ s` with it in the above.
